text: For anyone using Django 2.0;  you'll want to change your urls.py (in mysite/mysite) to:  from django.contrib import admin from django.urls import path, include  urlpatterns = [     path('admin/', admin.site.urls),     path('webapp/', include('webapp.urls')) ]  also, you can do the following for your mysite/webapp/urls.py file:  from django.urls import path  from . import views  urlpatterns = [ path('', views.index, name='index')]
